bans: Shakhti, Lorelei, Sepinroth

Generally opponent played better this generation: unblocked 3 strong artifacts and decided to rush while farming with vampire lords other side of the map. Had huge stats advantage and attacked but Brissa managed to hold off the attacks with larger army and more mana which exped her up to epxert air, earth and wisdom. While opponent had options to continue surrendered for non-h3 related reasons.

I got slightly better heroes, invested in Astral who was able to out-blind size-2 conservatory on 121. This was highly convenient as it allowed to lose both angels 122 to tan AI where anain with 1 week army magic-arrowed them, killing stonghold meat and only earth magic hero I had. On the same day Orange AI took my village in passage zone leaving making me really disappointed I did not have this on stream. But then 2 huts with earth magic and 1st roll TP(guild in same inferno village) allowed to do all the stuff we like: I ramped up magic heroes, obliterated pickets,  got resources for dd, cyclopes farmed experimental workshops, mages caught up with expansion. When entering new treasure zone I saw opponent farmed 2 conservatories there but as these were small and opponent stayed exposed, Astral was able to dd-catch, nomen omen, Aine and advantage in magic stats and army made final battle pretty one-sided.

All in all red colour and better hero development tipped the balance towards my side

Przez to stał gorzej z ekspansją, choć szybciej zrobił taras gryfów ("konsę") dwójkę. W 2. tygodniu dorwałem mu i zabiłem Aenaina na 2 aniołach, krótko potem porobił trochę wiwern, ale kosztem ostatniego anioła. Ostatecznie poddał z braku perspektyw, ja już w tym momencie miałem DD i szkoliłem kilku kontrolnych, więc raczej długo gra i tak by nie potrwała. Dzięki za grę!
